## Animações com Animated API

Sempre usar `useNativeDriver: true` para `opacity` e `transform`. Nunca para `width`, `height` ou `backgroundColor`.

### Padrão: glow pulsante (usado em CTAs)

```tsx
const glowOpacity = useRef(new Animated.Value(0.35)).current;

useEffect(() => {
  Animated.loop(
    Animated.sequence([
      Animated.timing(glowOpacity, { toValue: 0.9, duration: 1400, useNativeDriver: true }),
      Animated.timing(glowOpacity, { toValue: 0.35, duration: 1400, useNativeDriver: true }),
    ]),
  ).start();
}, [glowOpacity]);

// JSX: glow posicionado ANTES do elemento principal (z-order abaixo)
<View style={styles.ctaWrapper}>
  <Animated.View pointerEvents="none" style={[styles.ctaGlow, { opacity: glowOpacity }]} />
  <Button label="INICIAR" variant="primary" size="lg" fullWidth />
</View>
```

### Padrão: scale no press

```tsx
const scale = useRef(new Animated.Value(1)).current;
const onPressIn = () => Animated.spring(scale, { toValue: 0.96, useNativeDriver: true }).start();
const onPressOut = () => Animated.spring(scale, { toValue: 1, useNativeDriver: true }).start();
```

